<title>JAPAN: Hunet to buy back up to 160,000 shares.</title>
<headline>Hunet to buy back up to 160,000 shares.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Hunet Inc, a general contractor, said on Friday it has decided to buy back up to 160,000 of its own shares, or up to 80 million yen worth, to introduce a stock option scheme.</p>
<p>The plan is subject to approval at its shareholders' meeting on June 27.</p>
<p>Stock options will be offered to 20 directors and executives. Each director will have the option to buy between 5,000 and 10,000 shares, and each executive 1,000 to 5,000.</p>
<p>The repurchase plan will be carried out from April 1, 1998, to March 31, 2000.</p>
